The article announces the launch of a new initiative called Climate REDI, which aims to promote clean energy technologies in developing countries. It includes three new clean energy technology programs and funding for a renewable energy program under the World Bank's Strategic Climate Fund. The initiative will focus on accelerating the deployment of renewable energy and energy efficiency technologies, reducing greenhouse gas emissions, fighting energy poverty, and improving public health, particularly for vulnerable populations. The article also mentions the Major Economies Forum on Energy and Climate (MEF) and the release of ten Technology Action Plans developed under the Global Partnership on clean energy technologies. Additionally, Energy Secretary Steven Chu announces the hosting of a Clean Energy Ministerial in Washington, D.C., next year to drive concrete action on global clean energy technology deployment.